swMcastVlanMIB.name: swMcastVlanMIB

swISMVlanGlobalState.description: This indicates the global state of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swMSMVlanGlobalState.description: This indicates the global state of the MLD snooping multicast VLAN.

swISMVlanTable.name: swISMVlanTable

swISMVlanName.name: swISMVlanName
swISMVlanName.description: This indicates the VLAN name of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swISMVlanSourcePort.name: swISMVlanSourcePort
swISMVlanSourcePort.description: This indicates the port list of the source ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as tag ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports will be forwarded to the source ports.

swISMVlanMemberPort.name: swISMVlanMemberPort
swISMVlanMemberPort.description: This indicates the port list of the member ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as untagged ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports will be forwarded to the source ports.

swISMVlanTagMemberPort.name: swISMVlanTagMemberPort
swISMVlanTagMemberPort.description: This indicates the port list of the tag member ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swISMVlanUntagSourcePort.name: swISMVlanUntagSourcePort
swISMVlanUntagSourcePort.description: This indicates the untagged member ports to add to the multicast VLAN.

swISMVlanState.name: swISMVlanState
swISMVlanState.description: This can be used to enable or disable the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swISMVlanRepSourceAddrType.name: swISMVlanRepSourceAddrType
swISMVlanRepSourceAddrType.description: This is the type of multicast VLAN replacement address as specified by object 'swISMVlanRepSourceAddr'.

swISMVlanRepSourceAddr.name: swISMVlanRepSourceAddr
swISMVlanRepSourceAddr.description: This is the replacement address of this multicast VLAN.

swISMVlanRemapPriority.name: swISMVlanRemapPriority
swISMVlanRemapPriority.description: This is the priority value (0 to 7) to be associated with the data traffic to be forwarded on the multicast VLAN. When set to -1, the packet's original priority will be used.

swISMVlanReplacePriority.name: swISMVlanReplacePriority
swISMVlanReplacePriority.description: This specifies that a packet's priority will be changed by the switch based on the remap priority. This flag will only take effect when remap priority is set.

swISMVlanProfileIDList.name: swISMVlanProfileIDList
swISMVlanProfileIDList.description: This specifies a profile ID list for each VLAN ID of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.
